Cheesy Chicken Pasta
source|
url|http://insidebrucrewlife.com/2016/08/cheesy-chicken-pasta/
aliases|
tags|
activeTime|
totalTime|30 minutes
yield|6 servings
description|This Cheesy Chicken Pasta is an easy meal that you can make in under 30 minutes. Gooey cheese, pasta, and chicken will have everyone licking their plates clean.

# ingredients
8|oz|small pasta noodles
2|tbsp|butter
1/2|cup|diced red peppers
1|tbsp|minced garlic
2|tbsp|flour
1 1/2|cup|milk
3|cup|shredded cheddar jack cheese
1 to 13|oz|can chunk chicken (or 1 1/2 cups shredded chicken)
1|tbsp|ranch seasoning powder
||pepper to taste

# instructions
Prepare the noodles according to the package directions. Drain when finished cooking.
Melt the butter in a large skillet. Add the peppers and saut√© for 1-2 minutes. Add the garlic and flour and stir and cook for another 1-2 minutes.
Slowly whisk in the milk and cook on medium until thick. Add 2 cups of cheese and stir until melted and creamy.
Stir in the cooked pasta, chicken, ranch powder, and remaining cheese. Season to taste with pepper. Sprinkle a little bit of cheese on top right before serving, if desired. Serves 6.